Thou talk'st of nothing.


298
0:21:7,229 --> 0:21:8,931
True.


299
0:21:8,931 --> 0:21:13,234
True, I talk of dreams;


300
0:21:13,234 --> 0:21:18,739
which are the children
of an idle brain...


301
0:21:18,739 --> 0:21:23,243
Begot of nothing
but vain fantasy;


302
0:21:23,243 --> 0:21:27,747
which is as thin
of substance as the air,


303
0:21:27,747 --> 0:21:30,75
and more inconstant
than the wind


304
0:21:30,75 --> 0:21:34,252
who woos even now
the frozen bosom of the north,


305
0:21:34,252 --> 0:21:38,256
and being angered
puffs away from thence,


306
0:21:38,256 --> 0:21:45,563
turning his side
to the dew-dropping south.


307
0:21:45,563 --> 0:21:49,766
This wind you talk of
blows us from ourselves.


308
0:21:49,766 --> 0:21:59,775
Strike drum.
Come, lusty gentlemen.


309
0:21:59,775 --> 0:22:4,145
Romeo, we shall
arrive too late.


310
0:22:4,145 --> 0:22:8,216
I fear too early...


311
0:22:8,216 --> 0:22:10,717
For my mind misgives...


312
0:22:10,717 --> 0:22:14,221
Some consequence,
yet hanging in the stars,


313
0:22:14,221 --> 0:22:19,225
shall bitterly begin
his fearful date


314
0:22:19,225 --> 0:22:21,727
with this night's revels,


315
0:22:21,727 --> 0:22:24,73
and expire the term
of a despised life


316
0:22:24,73 --> 0:22:27,732
closed in my breast,


317
0:22:27,732 --> 0:22:37,741
by some vile forfeit
of untimely death.


318
0:22:37,741 --> 0:22:43,246
But he that hath
the steerage of my course...


319
0:22:43,246 --> 0:22:50,118
Direct my sail.


320
0:22:50,118 --> 0:22:54,256
Enter my poor house.
Vido, vido, welcome.


321
0:22:54,256 --> 0:22:59,26
Oh, my lovely Helena,
my lovely niece.


322
0:22:59,26 --> 0:23:2,196
Welcome all!
Be merry, gentlemen.


323
0:23:2,196 --> 0:23:5,198
Be lively, ladies.
Ahoy! Ahoy!


324
0:23:5,198 --> 0:23:6,699
Welcome, gentlemen.


325
0:23:6,699 --> 0:23:9,202
I have seen the day
that I have worn a visor


326
0:23:9,202 --> 0:23:11,703
and could tell a whispering tale
in a fair lady's ear,


327
0:23:11,703 --> 0:23:13,205
such as would please.


328
0:23:13,205 --> 0:23:16,208
'Tis gone, 'tis gone.
You are welcome, gentlemen.


329
0:23:16,208 --> 0:25:59,16
Ladies, ho, ho!


330
0:25:59,16 --> 0:26:5,155
She doth teach the torches
to burn bright.


331
0:26:5,155 --> 0:26:7,89
It seems she hangs
upon the cheek of night


332
0:26:7,89 --> 0:26:11,16
as a rich jewel
in an Ethiop's ear;,


333
0:26:11,16 --> 0:26:18,666
beauty too rich for use,
for earth too dear.


334
0:26:18,666 --> 0:26:22,203
So shows a snowy dove
trooping with crows,


335
0:26:22,203 --> 0:26:31,677
as yonder lady
o'er her fellow shows.


336
0:26:31,677 --> 0:26:34,46
Did my heart love till now?


337
0:26:34,46 --> 0:26:37,617
Forswear it sight,


338
0:26:37,617 --> 0:26:50,694
for I ne'er saw true beauty
till this night.


339
0:26:50,694 --> 0:27:0,77
This by his voice
should be a Montague.


340
0:27:0,77 --> 0:27:4,64
Uncle, this is
a Montague, our foe;


341
0:27:4,64 --> 0:27:6,642
a villain that is
hither come in spite,


342
0:27:6,642 --> 0:27:8,644
to scorn at
our solemnity this night.


343
0:27:8,644 --> 0:27:10,244
Young Romeo is it?


344
0:27:10,244 --> 0:27:12,647
Dares the slave come hither
covered in an antic face,


345
0:27:12,647 --> 0:27:14,482
to fear and scorn
at our solemnity?


346
0:27:14,482 --> 0:27:16,65
'A bears him like
a courtly gentleman;


347
0:27:16,65 --> 0:27:18,652
and to say truth,
Verona brags of him


348
0:27:18,652 --> 0:27:20,654
to be a virtuous
and well managed youth.


349
0:27:20,654 --> 0:27:22,656
I would not for the wealth
of all this town


350
0:27:22,656 --> 0:27:24,657
here in my house
do him disparagement.


351
0:27:24,657 --> 0:27:27,26
Therefore have patience,
take no note of him.


352
0:27:27,26 --> 0:27:29,662
The Moureska!


353
0:27:29,662 --> 0:29:4,556
The Moureska!


354
0:29:4,556 --> 0:29:7,559
Why, Uncle,
'tis a shame!


355
0:29:7,559 --> 0:29:9,127
Go to.


356
0:29:9,127 --> 0:29:11,562
You are a saucy boy.


357
0:29:11,562 --> 0:29:14,65
You'll make a mutiny
among my guests!


358
0:29:14,65 --> 0:29:16,567
Am I the master here,
or you?


359
0:29:16,567 --> 0:29:18,69
I will not endure him.


360
0:29:18,69 --> 0:29:20,27
You will not endure!
He shall be endured!


361
0:29:20,27 --> 0:29:23,573
Or I know what!


362
0:29:23,573 --> 0:29:35,83
Well said, my hearts.


363
0:29:35,83 --> 0:29:37,585
You're a princox.


364
0:29:37,585 --> 0:29:41,289
Be quiet or...


365
0:29:41,289 --> 0:29:47,94
Ah.


366
0:29:47,94 --> 0:30:55,486
For shame!
I'll make you quiet.


367
0:30:55,486 --> 0:30:59,156
Leonardo will sing!


368
0:30:59,156 --> 0:31:12,568
Leonardo, I pray thee, sing.


369
0:31:12,568 --> 0:31:16,438
What is a youth?


370
0:31:16,438 --> 0:31:20,241
Impetuous fire


371
0:31:20,241 --> 0:31:24,178
What is a maid?


372
0:31:24,178 --> 0:31:27,481
Ice and desire


373
0:31:27,481 --> 0:31:30,95
The world wags on


374
0:31:30,95 --> 0:31:35,455
A rose will bloom


375
0:31:35,455 --> 0:31:39,925
It then will fade


376
0:31:39,925 --> 0:31:44,429
So does a youth


377
0:31:44,429 --> 0:31:53,37
So does the fairest maid


378
0:31:53,37 --> 0:31:56,673
Comes the time


379
0:31:56,673 --> 0:31:58,174
When one sweet smile


380
0:31:58,174 --> 0:32:3,712
Has its season for a while


381
0:32:3,712 --> 0:32:9,617
Then love's in love with me


382
0:32:9,617 --> 0:32:13,454
Some may think only to marry


383
0:32:13,454 --> 0:32:17,9
Others will tease and tarry


384
0:32:17,9 --> 0:32:20,527
Mine is the very best parry


385
0:32:20,527 --> 0:32:24,263
Cupid he rules us all


386
0:32:24,263 --> 0:32:27,933
Caper the caper,
sing me the song


387
0:32:27,933 --> 0:32:31,403
Death will come soon
to hush us along


388
0:32:31,403 --> 0:32:34,939
Sweeter than honey
and bitter as gall


389
0:32:34,939 --> 0:32:38,542
Love is a pastime
that never will pall


390
0:32:38,542 --> 0:32:42,613
Sweeter than honey
