394
0:33:16,176 --> 0:33:23,82
So does a youth


395
0:33:23,82 --> 0:33:34,324
So does the fairest maid


396
0:33:34,324 --> 0:33:38,595
If I profane
with my unworthiest hand


397
0:33:38,595 --> 0:33:41,97
this holy shrine,


398
0:33:41,97 --> 0:33:44,233
the gentle sin is this;


399
0:33:44,233 --> 0:33:50,505
my lips, two blushing pilgrims,
ready stand


400
0:33:50,505 --> 0:33:57,411
to smooth the rough touch
with a gentle kiss.


401
0:33:57,411 --> 0:34:14,59
Oh.


402
0:34:14,59 --> 0:34:20,64
Good pilgrim, you do wrong
your hand too much


403
0:34:20,64 --> 0:34:24,68
which mannerly devotion
shows in this;


404
0:34:24,68 --> 0:34:28,571
for saints have hands
that pilgrims' hands do touch


405
0:34:28,571 --> 0:34:33,575
and palm to palm is
holy palmers' kiss.


406
0:34:33,575 --> 0:34:37,579
Have not saints lips,
and holy palmers too?


407
0:34:37,579 --> 0:34:41,582
Ay, pilgrim, lips that
they must use in prayer.


408
0:34:41,582 --> 0:34:43,84
Oh...


409
0:34:43,84 --> 0:34:47,88
O then, dear saint,


410
0:34:47,88 --> 0:34:56,595
let lips do
what hands do...


411
0:34:56,595 --> 0:35:2,34
They pray,
grant thou,


412
0:35:2,34 --> 0:35:4,536
lest faith
turn to despair.


413
0:35:4,536 --> 0:35:6,538
Saints do not move,


414
0:35:6,538 --> 0:35:8,54
though grants
for prayers' sake.


415
0:35:8,54 --> 0:35:14,44
Then move not...


416
0:35:14,44 --> 0:35:20,49
While my prayer's
effect I take.


417
0:35:20,49 --> 0:35:27,55
Thus from my lips,
by thine,


418
0:35:27,55 --> 0:35:40,568
my sin is purged.


419
0:35:40,568 --> 0:35:44,571
Then have my lips the sin
that they have took.


420
0:35:44,571 --> 0:35:46,573
Sin from my lips!


421
0:35:46,573 --> 0:35:48,575
O trespass sweetly urged!


422
0:35:48,575 --> 0:35:53,245
Give me my sin again.


423
0:35:53,245 --> 0:35:58,82
