424
0:35:58,82 --> 0:36:1,352
It then will fade


425
0:36:1,352 --> 0:36:7,49
So does a youth


426
0:36:7,49 --> 0:36:29,209
So does the fairest maid


427
0:36:29,209 --> 0:36:30,544
Juliet!


428
0:36:30,544 --> 0:36:33,213
Lady Juliet!


429
0:36:33,213 --> 0:36:34,982
Nurse?


430
0:36:34,982 --> 0:36:40,653
Your mother craves
a word with you.


431
0:36:40,653 --> 0:36:48,59
Make haste, make haste!


432
0:36:48,59 --> 0:36:49,561
What is her mother?


433
0:36:49,561 --> 0:36:51,62
Hmm.
Merry, bachelor,


434
0:36:51,62 --> 0:36:54,64
her mother is
the lady of the house,


435
0:36:54,64 --> 0:36:57,67
and a good lady,
and wise, and virtuous;


436
0:36:57,67 --> 0:36:59,569
I nursed her daughter
that you talked withal.


437
0:36:59,569 --> 0:37:6,508
Hmm.


438
0:37:6,508 --> 0:37:9,511
I tell you he that
shall lay hold of her


439
0:37:9,511 --> 0:37:13,749
shall have the chinks.


440
0:37:13,749 --> 0:37:18,919
Is she a Capulet?


441
0:37:18,919 --> 0:37:22,22
Ah, dear account!


442
0:37:22,22 --> 0:37:30,262
My life is my foe's debt.


443
0:37:30,262 --> 0:37:33,232
What, ho, my mistresses?


444
0:37:33,232 --> 0:37:35,34
What, will you be gone?


445
0:37:35,34 --> 0:37:37,535
It seems so, poor God,
it is so very late.


446
0:37:37,535 --> 0:37:39,804
We'll call it early,
by and by.


447
0:37:39,804 --> 0:37:47,44
Good night,
sweet, my Lady Juliet.


448
0:37:47,44 --> 0:37:48,545
Come hither, nurse.


449
0:37:48,545 --> 0:37:50,547
Hmm?


450
0:37:50,547 --> 0:37:52,182
What is yon gentleman?


451
0:37:52,182 --> 0:37:53,549
Count Paris.


452
0:37:53,549 --> 0:37:59,188
No. What's he
that follows there?


453
0:37:59,188 --> 0:38:0,989
Oh! I know not.


454
0:38:0,989 --> 0:38:5,493
Go, ask his name.


455
0:38:5,493 --> 0:38:8,495
Hmm. Romeo, of
the house of Montague.


456
0:38:8,495 --> 0:38:10,13
What?


457
0:38:10,13 --> 0:38:13,133
His name is Romeo,
and a Montague;


458
0:38:13,133 --> 0:38:22,508
the only son of
your great enemy.


459
0:38:22,508 --> 0:38:27,512
My only love sprung
from my only hate,


460
0:38:27,512 --> 0:38:34,518
too early seen unknown,
and known too late!


461
0:38:34,518 --> 0:38:36,2
Oh!


462
0:38:36,2 --> 0:38:39,22
Prodigious birth of love
it is to me


463
0:38:39,22 --> 0:38:51,533
that I must love
a loathed enemy.


464
0:38:51,533 --> 0:38:53,35
Juliet!


465
0:38:53,35 --> 0:38:55,57
My Lady Juliet!


466
0:38:55,57 --> 0:38:59,4
Madam!


467
0:38:59,4 --> 0:39:6,813
Romeo!


468
0:39:6,813 --> 0:39:9,482
Juliet!


469
0:39:9,482 --> 0:39:12,985
Romeo!


470
0:39:12,985 --> 0:39:16,921
Lady Juliet!


471
0:39:16,921 --> 0:39:18,49
Juliet!


472
0:39:18,49 --> 0:39:25,496
Romeo!


473
